name: d/united-technologies | Dec. 29, 2011 | Namecoin
description:
Domain: d/united-technologies
Mint Date: Dec. 29, 2011

This gives ownership to the united-technologies.bit domain and can be unwrapped to point the domain to a server hosting content.

More importantly though, this is one of the earliest domain name NFTs ever stored on a blockchain. Namecoin was the first fork of Bitcoin and the first to store domain names in a blockchain. 

People used Namecoin to register private domain names on-chain along with other details such as their bitcoin address, profile/splash images, their occupation, etc. 

Domain names stored on Namecoin were among the first NFTs ever made!

Comes with 2 NMC in the vault, which should be enough for over 100+ years of auto-renewals. 

All names registered on Namecoin have a prefix (ie: d/ , u/ , i/) which is a way to categorize their use.  d/ = domain

xn-- is a prefix for punycode which can be translated at punycoder.com. 



View contents of NFT by expanding Properties Below and at Emblem.Finance 👇

[View this NFT on Emblem.Finance](https://emblem.finance/nft?id=11655579725018421)

NMC Explorer: [NGRrQYcnEaCXwzV6iHFwmwtDJMWBZK8iLp](https://nmc.tokenview.com/en/address/NGRrQYcnEaCXwzV6iHFwmwtDJMWBZK8iLp)
